Polymorphism ka matlab hai:
Ek method ya object ka multiple forms mein behave karna â€” depending on context.

Java mein 2 types hote hain:

âœŒï¸ Types of Polymorphism:
Type	Meaning	Also Called As
1. Compile-time Polymorphism	Method call decide hota hai compile time pe	Method Overloading
2. Runtime Polymorphism	Method call decide hota hai runtime pe	Method Overriding
1ï¸âƒ£ Method Overloading (Compile-time)
ğŸ‘‰ Same class me same method name with different parameters

java
Copy
Edit
class Calculator {
    int add(int a, int b) {
        return a + b;
    }

    double add(double a, double b) {
        return a + b;
    }
}
java
Copy
Edit
Calculator calc = new Calculator();
System.out.println(calc.add(5, 3));       // int version
System.out.println(calc.add(2.5, 4.7));   // double version
âœ… Method name same, but signature (params) different

2ï¸âƒ£ Method Overriding (Runtime)
ğŸ‘‰ Parent-child mein same method signature
ğŸ‘‰ Runtime pe decide hota hai kiska method chalega

java
Copy
Edit
class Animal {
    void sound() {
        System.out.println("Animal sound");
    }
}

class Dog extends Animal {
    @Override
    void sound() {
        System.out.println("Dog barks");
    }
}
java
Copy
Edit
Animal a = new Dog();  // reference = Animal, object = Dog
a.sound();  // Output: Dog barks
âœ… Runtime pe decide hua ki Dog ka method call hoga

